The '''J. Chokka Rao Devadula lift irrigation scheme''' is a [[lift irrigation scheme]] in [[India]].<ref>http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-16/hyderabad/29781230_1_devadula-workers-tunnel</ref> It is the second biggest of its kind in [[Asia]]. Devadula is the place in [[Warangal District]], [[Telangana]], where the scheme's intake well is located.<ref>http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2011-07-18/hyderabad/29786709_1_devadula-project-site-bodies</ref><ref>http://www.financialexpress.com/news/hcc-bags-devadula-lift-irrigation-phase-iii-order/345426/</ref>
==The Project== The project is specially designed to lift water from the [[River Godavari]] to irrigate more than {{convert|600000|acre|km2}} in the [[drought]] prone [[Telangana]] state, India. Later it was named after the politician J. Chokkarao as the 'J. Chokkarao Devadula lift irrigation scheme'. The total work was divided into three phases for executional convenience in the year 2003 .
The minimum river water level required is 73 m [[Mean sea level|MSL]] in the river to pump the water whereas the non-monsoon / lean season river water level is below 71 m MSL. No downstream weir is yet constructed to build up the river minimum water level at this location of the river.
The maximum water lift is by 510 meters. The project operational requirement is 484 [[Megawatt|MW]] power and 1.4 billion [[KWh]] of electrical energy annually for pumping 38 [[Tmcft]] water.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.irrigation.telangana.gov.in/icad/projects|title=J.C.R. DEVADULA LIFT IRRIGATION SCHEME|accessdate=19 July 2015}}</ref> This lift canal is an inter river basin transfer link by feeding Godavari River water to [[Krishna River]] basin in Warangal and Nalgonda districts.
==Honour== The project was renamed to honour [[J. Chokka Rao]], a freedom fighter from [[Karimnagar]].
