'''Margaret J. Gamper''' (1907<ref>{{cite book|author=National Library of Medicine (U.S.)|title=National Library of Medicine Catalog|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TFxPAQAAIAAJ|year=1955|publisher=Judd & Detweiler|page=565}}</ref>&ndash; March 18, 2002) was a pioneer of modern natural childbirth.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Young|first1=Marybeth|title=Margaret Gamper: A pioneer in childbirth education|journal=Geriatric Nursing|date=July 1986|volume=7|issue=4|pages=210–211|doi=10.1016/s0197-4572(86)80095-7|pmid=3636265}}</ref><ref name=latimes>{{cite news|title=Margaret Gamper, 94; Nurse, Early Advocate of Natural Childbirth|url=http://articles.latimes.com/2002/mar/27/local/me-gamper27|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=March 27, 2002}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Adrienne B. Lieberman|title=Easing Labor Pain: The Complete Guide to a More Comfortable and Rewarding Birth|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=4U0Qb1vPMrYC&pg=PT54|year=1992|publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt|isbn=1-55832-636-7|page=46}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author=Barbara Harper, R.N.|title=Gentle Birth Choices|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=3aetgBOUdVMC&pg=PA109|year=2005|publisher=Inner Traditions / Bear & Co|isbn=978-1-59477-863-6|page=109}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Margaret Gamper|journal=International Journal of Childbirth Education|date=June 2002|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1P3-135260081.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kapos|first1=Shia|title=Margaret J. Gamper, 94|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2002-03-24/news/0203240433_1_childbirth-educator-expectant-mothers-birthing-rooms|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|date=March 24, 2002}}</ref> One of Gamper's students was Dr. Robert Bradley, who developed the [[Bradley method of natural childbirth]].<ref name=latimes/> Gamper wrote two books on childbirth, "Relax, Here's Your Baby" and "Preparation for the Heir Minded".
