'''Roger Gerrard Breeze''' (10 October 1946 - 14 June 2016) was an English [[veterinary scientist]] who was an expert on [[bio-terrorism]] and a critic of mass culling to combat [[foot and mouth disease]] in animals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/professor-roger-breeze-j032gf7df|title=Professor Roger Breeze|work=thetimes.co.uk|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/washingtonpost/obituary.aspx?n=roger-gerrard-breeze&pid=180345805&fhid=6125|title=ROGER GERRARD BREEZE's Obituary on The Washington Post|work=legacy.com|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/obituaries/2016/09/29/roger-breeze-expert-in-animal-diseases--obituary/|title=Roger Breeze, expert in animal diseases – obituary|work=telegraph.co.uk|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref> == References == {{Reflist}}
